@node Main "Locale"

    A1200 ONLY...

                                Locale

        The Locate preferences editor allows you to change the language
that the Amiga and any  Locate-compatible programs use when displayed text
on the screen. Not all programs have been written to handle localisation 
and so very few of the current crop with take advantage of any language
settings that you make. When you load up the Locate editor, you'll see a
very impressive map of the world with a single white area marked somewhere
on the map. This aspect of the editor allows you to control the time zone
relative to GMT. Above this are two gadgets labelled Available Languages
and Preferred Languages. Inside the first of these two gadgets should be a
list of the languages available on your system - just click on the one (or
ones) that you want to set the language you'd like to work in.


